[base] > - Computes `ship_lag` as `date_diff(sold_date.date, ship_date.date, day)` (note: the args are swapped from the question — `date_diff(end, start, unit)` — so ship_lag is positive when ship_date is after sold_date)
[base] > - Groups by: first 20 characters of warehouse name, ship_mode type, and lowercased call center name
[base] > - Buckets order counts into 5 columns: ≤30, 31-60, 61-90, 91-120, >120 days
[base] > - Orders with nulls first (Trilogy defaults to `asc` which puts nulls first)
[base] > - Returns up to 100 rows
[base] > 
[base] > Run completed in 280ms. The data shows all shipping lags are ≤90 days in this dataset (lag_91_120 and lag_gt_120 are all 0).
